What’s really bad about this situation is that I had already talked with Michelle Rushing, Area Director, about a situation regarding the CB at the Goodman Theatre, 56 W. Randolph. I had ordered the Power Greens Shrimp Salad and I left the CB with no salad or refund money. I thought the situation would get better after talking with Ms. Rushing. I was wrong. I decided to go to the Corner Bakery on Washington and Wells. A young girl named Raven was at the register. When she saw that I had my “Be My Guest” certificates, she gave me attitude and unprofessionalism. With “Be My Guest” certificates, the staff knows that they came from corporate for a bad experience. So, I guess this individual named Raven was going to come off ignorant and uncouth to me because I complained about service at a CB. What she failed to realize is that if I had got good service in the first place, I would not have had to call corporate on any CB. For example, when I went to pay for the order, she was staring at the certificates in my hand. So, we both were just staring at them. After around 30 seconds, she looked up at me and with attitude asked, “You go be using them?” I just looked at her. Totally ridiculous. I don’t know if there is re-training that is needed or if this is just the CB way, but there really needs to be some re-training. Walking pass customers and not greeting them or giving them attitude isn’t going to cut it in downtown Chicago where there are numerous eateries and the competition is fierce to get customers and keep them.

This used to be my go to place for lunch when downtown for work. The sandwiches used to be delicious, quality ingredients, and well made. It was worth the money. I was even known in my office for always going to this corner bakery for lunch. Over the last few months the food has not been the same. First, I had a sandwich that wasn’t well made, it was put together sloppy and just didn’t taste the same. I know it’s busy at lunch so figured it was a fluke. I went back again, ordered a sandwich and again it was just so-so. I tried a few more times and equally disappointed.  Yesterday is the last time I’ll be going here, my chicken in the chicken pesto sandwich was hard and chewy and I just don’t think the ingredients are the same or as fresh anymore. What happened to this corner bakery? It used to be my favorite place to eat and was so yummy. It now seems low quality and not somewhere I’ll be returning unfortunately. I couldn’t even eat my sandwich yesterday it was that chewy and gross. :(

I had ordered the choose two with a sandwich that had Turkey, bacon, avocado, tomato & mayo, the second dish I chose was the shrimp linguini. Everything about the sandwich was delicious. The bacon! The Turkey! The avocado! You can tell they use high quality, fresh ingredients. The linguini was really good as well! It had a ton of flavor. Just the right balance of garlic & herbs. The mixed greens salad came with an Italian dressing already on it. Kinda tasted like olive garden's (but WAY better). My daughter had ordered an avocado egg bowl.
